      <hedline>
        <hl1>June 18-24; Escalating in Colombia</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ERIC SCHMITT</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Senate approved nearly $1 billion in aid to Colombia, a major escalation in America's commitment to help an important Latin American ally combat drug trafficking and a guerrilla insurgency.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Senate approved nearly $1 billion in aid to Colombia, a major escalation in America's commitment to help an important Latin American ally combat drug trafficking and a guerrilla insurgency.</p>
        <p>The House has already approved the measure, a top priority of the Clinton administration. Proponents said the aid, including helicopters, would be used to train and equip three army battalions for counter-drug operations. But critics warned that Washington was plunging into an open-ended civil conflict that has cost thousands of lives over nearly four decades.</p>
        <p>ERIC SCHMITT</p>
      </block>
